## Key Pitfalls

| Pitfall | Guidance |
|---------|----------|
| **`Thread.Abort` â†’ `PlatformNotSupportedException`** | There is no .NET 8 equivalent. You *must* use cooperative cancellation. |
| **`Thread.Interrupt` is also obsolete** | Don't substitute one for the other; both require migration. |
| **Race condition in original code** | `Channel<T>` eliminates the lost-signal bug entirely â€” no manual lock/event needed. |
| **Not disposing `CancellationTokenSource`** | Always dispose it; leaking causes timer/callback leaks. |
| **Assuming cancellation is instant** | If `Handle(item)` is long-running, pass `token` into it and check periodically. |
| **Swallowing `OperationCanceledException`** | Only catch at the top-level loop boundary, not deeper in the stack. |

